<recipe>
    <name>Steck Pepper Steak</name>
    <indexCharacter>S</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Cut steak diagonally across grain into thin strips. Heat corn oil and add garlic, cook until browned slightly. Add meat and cook until browned. Mix in onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ginger. Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until tender. Blend cornstarch with bullion and stir into pan. Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, until liquid is thickened.</instructions>
